00:00:28,495 --> 00:00:30,497
[ Laughs ]

00:00:34,468 --> 00:00:36,803
♪♪

00:00:36,803 --> 00:00:37,938
Narrator: First into the Tank

00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:40,407
is a product designed to
relieve stress

00:00:40,407 --> 00:00:42,442
and promote relaxation.

00:00:42,442 --> 00:00:47,347
♪♪

00:00:47,347 --> 00:00:51,785
♪♪

00:00:51,785 --> 00:00:53,987
Hi, Sharks.
My name is Kaylin Marcotte.

00:00:53,987 --> 00:00:57,824
I am from New York City,
and I'm here seeking $500,000

00:00:57,824 --> 00:01:00,394
in exchange for
5% of my company.

00:01:00,394 --> 00:01:01,395
Wow.

00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:02,796
Stress and mental exhaustion

00:01:02,796 --> 00:01:06,934
can wreak havoc on our minds,
bodies, and relationships.

00:01:06,934 --> 00:01:09,770
Five years ago,
I was working around the clock

00:01:09,770 --> 00:01:11,738
at an early start‐up
and was looking

00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:16,310
for a new and healthy way
to unwind and unplug.

00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:17,878
I tried meditation, yoga,

00:01:17,878 --> 00:01:21,582
even essential oils
without much success.

00:01:21,582 --> 00:01:25,652
And then this tiny object
changed everything.

00:01:25,652 --> 00:01:27,521
A jigsaw puzzle.

00:01:27,521 --> 00:01:29,489
Focusing on one simple task

00:01:29,489 --> 00:01:31,625
and building something
piece by piece

00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:34,561
felt both relaxing
and rewarding.

00:01:34,561 --> 00:01:36,597
I lost the urge
to check my phone

00:01:36,597 --> 00:01:37,898
and truly cleared my head.

00:01:37,898 --> 00:01:40,734
Problem was, all
the puzzles on the market

00:01:40,734 --> 00:01:43,537
are outdated, uninspired,

00:01:43,537 --> 00:01:46,073
and, well, kind of lame.

00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:48,475
[ Laughter ]

00:01:48,475 --> 00:01:51,345
Sharks, let me
introduce you to Jiggy ‐‐

00:01:51,345 --> 00:01:53,714
modern puzzles with a mission.

00:01:53,714 --> 00:01:55,682
Each Jiggy features unique art

00:01:55,682 --> 00:01:58,785
by an emerging female artist
from around the world.

00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:02,556
A percentage of every sale
goes directly to that artist,

00:02:02,556 --> 00:02:04,758
empowering these
up‐and‐coming creatives

00:02:04,758 --> 00:02:07,594
and giving them a platform
to showcase their work.

00:02:07,594 --> 00:02:09,796
Each puzzle comes
in a reusable glass jar

00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:13,634
and includes simple tools
to preserve your work of art.

00:02:13,634 --> 00:02:14,868
When the final piece
is in place,

00:02:14,868 --> 00:02:17,638
simply spread our puzzle glue
over the pieces

00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:20,774
and transform it into a
beautifully crafted art print.

00:02:20,774 --> 00:02:23,744
We are reinventing
the humble jigsaw puzzle

00:02:23,744 --> 00:02:27,614
and reconnecting people
with both mindfulness and art,

00:02:27,614 --> 00:02:29,783
one piece at a time.

00:02:29,783 --> 00:02:32,886
Now, who's ready to
get Jiggy with us?

00:02:32,886 --> 00:02:35,522
In front of you,
you have some puzzles,

00:02:35,522 --> 00:02:36,590
each a different artwork.

00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:37,858
Oh, it's beautiful.
Cuban: That's cool.

00:02:37,858 --> 00:02:40,227
The pieces come in this
reusable glass jar.

00:02:40,227 --> 00:02:43,797
We've seen people use them as
a cookie jar or a flower vase.
Greiner: It's pretty.

00:02:43,797 --> 00:02:46,066
Behind it is
a tube of puzzle glue,

00:02:46,066 --> 00:02:49,469
and then in front is
a gold straight‐edge tool.

00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:50,570
It helps spread the glue.

00:02:50,570 --> 00:02:53,740
How long does it take?
These pieces are tiny.

00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:56,376
How many pieces
are in a typical puzzle?

00:02:56,376 --> 00:02:57,744
Probably 500 to 1,000.

00:02:57,744 --> 00:03:00,814
Our kids and I, my wife
and I love doing puzzles,

00:03:00,814 --> 00:03:02,816
but you need to
solve one puzzle for me.

00:03:02,816 --> 00:03:04,051
How did you get
to this valuation?

00:03:04,051 --> 00:03:06,920
Because it really is
very intimidating.
Yeah.

00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,056
Yeah, so, we just launched
nine months ago.

00:03:09,056 --> 00:03:12,426
In the last nine months, we have
done $1.6 million in sales.

00:03:12,426 --> 00:03:13,727
What? Wow.
Cuban: Good for you.

00:03:13,727 --> 00:03:16,697
This first year,
we're going to do 2.25.

00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:17,798
We're profitable.

00:03:17,798 --> 00:03:20,734
Tell me,
did you do that alone?

00:03:20,734 --> 00:03:22,369
Yes, I'm a one‐woman show.

00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:23,804
Oh, my gosh.
And you own 100%?

00:03:23,804 --> 00:03:25,806
Yeah.
Bootstrapped, no debt.

00:03:25,806 --> 00:03:27,808
Good for you.
Good for you.
No investors.
No equity partners.

00:03:27,808 --> 00:03:30,677
Very impressive.
Your timing was unique,
lucky, and perfect,

00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:33,580
because all of a sudden,
you're into COVID.

00:03:33,580 --> 00:03:34,815
Everybody's at home,

00:03:34,815 --> 00:03:36,917
and you're getting
this huge ramp.
Marcotte: Right.

00:03:36,917 --> 00:03:38,719
What was your profit
on that $1.6 million?

00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:40,554
We're netting 40%,

00:03:40,554 --> 00:03:42,389
so this year
on a two and a quarter,

00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:43,490
we're gonna make 900.

00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:44,658
That's unbelievable.
Wow!

00:03:44,658 --> 00:03:46,326
So why do you
need us?

00:03:46,326 --> 00:03:47,761
So, I'm doing this alone.

00:03:47,761 --> 00:03:49,529
I'm here for a partner.

00:03:49,529 --> 00:03:50,697
The incumbents in this space

00:03:50,697 --> 00:03:54,434
are following a retail,
kind of old‐school playbook.

00:03:54,434 --> 00:03:55,669
No one is digitally native.

00:03:55,669 --> 00:03:58,572
No one is competing in SEO
and digital marketing.

00:03:58,572 --> 00:03:59,840
It's like a land grab right now.

00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,641
You're doing it
all online?

00:04:01,641 --> 00:04:05,579
This first year is going to be
60% D2C, 40% wholesale.

00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:07,380
We were approached
earlier this year

00:04:07,380 --> 00:04:09,683
by an upscale national retailer,

00:04:09,683 --> 00:04:12,452
and we're going to be
in 215 stores.

00:04:12,452 --> 00:04:13,920
What does
a puzzle sell for?

00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:17,457
So, we retail these
for $40 and $48.

00:04:17,457 --> 00:04:18,592
Costs you what
to make them?

00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:19,826
$10.
$10.

00:04:19,826 --> 00:04:21,561
And how much
does the artist get?

00:04:21,561 --> 00:04:22,863
The artist makes, on average,

00:04:22,863 --> 00:04:25,732
$3,000 to $5,000
for our first run.

00:04:25,732 --> 00:04:29,736
What percentage of
the buyers now are repeat?

00:04:29,736 --> 00:04:31,772
First, we surveyed
our customers.

00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:33,940
We are expanding this category.

00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:37,310
Half of our customers had never
bought a jigsaw puzzle before.

00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:37,811
Ever?

00:04:37,811 --> 00:04:40,981
25% indicated 8 to 10
on a scale of 10

00:04:40,981 --> 00:04:43,650
that they would want
even something monthly.

00:04:43,650 --> 00:04:45,085
25%?
Like a subscription membership.

00:04:45,085 --> 00:04:47,821
You're suggesting there might be
a subscription model to this?

00:04:47,821 --> 00:04:50,791
Yes. We would curate
new, monthly images.

00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:52,926
What we're seeing is
people who do return

00:04:52,926 --> 00:04:55,462
are buying, on average,
four puzzles.

00:04:55,462 --> 00:04:57,798
What happens when
COVID is gone?

00:04:57,798 --> 00:05:00,467
These macro trends that
inspired me to start this,

00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:03,537
of self‐care and analog,

00:05:03,537 --> 00:05:04,805
those have been around
for a long time.

00:05:04,805 --> 00:05:07,841
We did a quarter million in our
first four months, pre‐COVID,

00:05:07,841 --> 00:05:09,843
and then we sold out.
Wow.

00:05:09,843 --> 00:05:11,778
You are great
at branding.
Thank you.

00:05:11,778 --> 00:05:14,581
Kaylin, first of all,
you're a supernova.

00:05:14,581 --> 00:05:15,782
Thank you.

00:05:15,782 --> 00:05:18,685
I'm trying to remember
if we've ever had somebody

00:05:18,685 --> 00:05:21,555
go from zero
to your kind of numbers.

00:05:21,555 --> 00:05:23,056
This is
a great business,

00:05:23,056 --> 00:05:27,360
but at the $10 million
value that you're implying,

00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:28,528
I have to believe

00:05:28,528 --> 00:05:30,864
that your sales are gonna be
tens of millions

00:05:30,864 --> 00:05:32,966
for me to recoup
my investment.

00:05:32,966 --> 00:05:37,838
I don't see it continuing
at that trajectory.

00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:41,174
I think people will
move on to other things.

00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,242
I'm out.

00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:44,811
Kaylin, you're
incredibly impressive.

00:05:44,811 --> 00:05:46,713
One of the most impressive
people I've seen

00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:48,014
in a very long time.
Thank you.

00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:52,719
I do think that you're
benefiting from the COVID push,

00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:55,021
and the valuation
is not the right valuation,

00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:56,857
but I also don't think
you need a Shark.

00:05:56,857 --> 00:05:58,792
So for that reason,
I'm out.

00:05:58,792 --> 00:06:00,894
Thank you.
I appreciate that.
And best wishes.

00:06:00,894 --> 00:06:04,364
You know, I'm struggling with
how much of this is sustainable,

00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:05,365
